1
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:13,767
<i>I felt bad because Emma left us,
Mom.</i>

2
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,967
<i>So you can't blame me
for falling for Jade.</i>

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,900
<i>Danilo threw away everything
we had.</i>

4
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:22,667
<i>I will make Jade realize that
she fought the wrong person.</i>

5
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,433
<i>I will do everything
to change my life.</i>

6
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,200
<i> Auntie Jade is nice to us.</i>

7
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:29,500
<i> And she does things...</i>

8
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:32,167
<i>that Mom is supposed
to be doing.</i>

9
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>Ligaya is getting on my nerves.</i>

10
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,367
<i> She must not know</i>

11
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:39,800
<i>that Olive Caparas is still very
much alive.</i>

12
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,467
<i> You really are a monster.</i>

13
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,300
<i> Monster!</i>

14
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:43,367
<i> Aunt Jade?</i>

15
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:44,567
<i> Ligaya, wait!</i>

16
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:45,833
<i> Mookie!</i>

17
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:48,967
<i>I think I heard her calling me.</i>

18
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:51,900
<i>I was talking to your
grandmother, but on the phone.</i>

19
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:54,133
<i>What did she say?
Where is she?</i>

20
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,600
<i> She went back to Cebu.</i>

21
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,233
Are you okay, Mookie?

22
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:39,200
Are you sad
that your grandmother left?

23
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:44,000
She and Mom are the same.

24
00:01:45,133 --> 00:01:46,600
She didn't think about me.

25
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:51,700
Forget about that, Mookie.

26
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:55,133
Your grandmother is just mad
at me.

27
00:01:56,733 --> 00:02:02,300
Are you also mad at me
for being with your Dad?

28
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:09,367
Honestly, Aunt Jade,
I feel guilty.

29
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:13,233
I feel like I'm betraying Mom.

30
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:16,300
Mookie,

31
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,667
I have something to tell you.

32
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,100
So you listen to me, okay?

33
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:27,000
Do you know why you're feeling
this way?

34
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:28,833
You feel guilty

35
00:02:28,967 --> 00:02:32,367
even though you're the one
who is left behind.

36
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:37,567
Because you're letting
your heart take over too much.

37
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:41,067
Sometimes, you have to be
strong.

38
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,800
You have to be brave.

39
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:45,067
So what if your grandmother
isn't here?

40
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,433
So what if Emma isn't here?

41
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:51,433
Show them you can live alone.

42
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:55,033
Don't forget that, Mookie.

43
00:02:55,167 --> 00:02:56,900
You must fight.

44
00:02:58,033 --> 00:03:02,667
You must fight always.

45
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,867
Okay?

46
00:03:15,133 --> 00:03:16,467
Come on.

47
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,733
Just give it a try.

48
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:19,200
Here.

49
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,900
This one's actually yours.

50
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:23,567
Cheers!

51
00:03:34,533 --> 00:03:35,767
Are you okay?

52
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:40,633
I'll just use the restroom,
Aunt Jade.

53
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:41,633
Okay.

54
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,267
- I'll be here.
- Okay.

55
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,833
Is that Mookie?

56
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:57,567
What?

57
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:06,700
OMG.

58
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,933
Look who's here.

59
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:12,333
I heard your mom
is never coming back.

60
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:14,000
Is that why you're here?

61
00:04:15,067 --> 00:04:19,067
Oh my god. Poor Mookie.

62
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,700
Her mom's never coming back
for her.

63
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:24,100
Here, drinks.

64
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,000
Do you want some?

65
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:30,767
Oh my god, I'm so sorry!

66
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:34,167
Are you okay?

67
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,833
Oh my god, you look so wet.

68
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,900
Oh my god!

69
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,133
No!

70
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:59,700
Stop! What? Stop! What now?

71
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,800
Stop it, Mookie!

72
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:04,600
I've been holding back
for a long time!

73
00:05:04,733 --> 00:05:06,467
- Me, too!
- That's enough!

74
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:15,967
You'll regret this!
We're not done yet.

75
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,800
Do you think this is over? No!

76
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,567
Go and be together!

77
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,467
Mookie, why did you do that?

78
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:30,633
They deserve that, Zayn.

79
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:31,733
What?

80
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:33,800
You weren't like that before.

81
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:35,533
Why do you seem to change?

82
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:40,400
I used to believe
that I should stay nice

83
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:42,133
despite being bullied.

84
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:44,200
But Aunt Jade is right.

85
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:48,133
It feels good when you fight

86
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:50,667
and don't let anyone oppress
you.

87
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:53,667
I prefer the good Mookie.

88
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,600
I thought you were different.

89
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:08,667
Very good, Mookie.

90
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:11,200
I'm so proud of you.

91
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,667
Cheers, baby girl.

92
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,333
That's my girl.

93
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,967
Really?

94
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:50,433
What are you doing?
That's too much.

95
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,800
Enough. Look at your eyeshadow.

96
00:07:53,933 --> 00:07:57,067
You're even putting on
too much lipstick.

97
00:07:58,367 --> 00:07:59,467
Mookie?

98
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,333
You're not listening to me.

99
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,667
Hello?

100
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,533
Why?

101
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:13,333
Doesn't it look good?

102
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:15,400
No.

103
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,767
Your makeup is so dark.

104
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:21,633
Natural suits you better.

105
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,167
We need to check those, too.

106
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:40,467
- Okay.
- Okay?

107
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,800
I'll be right back.

108
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:43,300
Double time, okay?

109
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:47,400
Please clean the corners, too.

110
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:48,733
Is everything okay over there?

111
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:37,567
Guys, if you want anything,
it's on me.

112
00:09:39,533 --> 00:09:41,400
Because...

113
00:09:41,533 --> 00:09:45,200
thank you, Aunt Jade!

114
00:09:46,933 --> 00:09:53,067
Since I'm already 18,
we can order anything we want!

115
00:09:57,167 --> 00:09:58,900
Waiter!

116
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:00,600
Waiter.

117
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:02,600
Miss, hi.

118
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:05,767
What's good?

119
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:07,100
I'll have this.

120
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:11,600
This one, Miss.
Four bottles of this, please.

121
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:13,767
Thank you.
And here's my card!

122
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:15,533
Wait!

123
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:16,900
No!

124
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,567
Wait!

125
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:21,133
Why aren't you drinking?

126
00:10:21,267 --> 00:10:22,367
This can't be.

127
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:26,633
This can't be! Shot!
We should drink!

128
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:28,533
Mooks, that's enough.

129
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:30,800
What the hell?
All of us are having fun.

130
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:32,800
- Right, girls?
- Yes!

131
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:35,300
Shot!

132
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:47,533
- There you go! Cheers!
- Cheers!

133
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,400
This is 10,000.

134
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,833
Okay!

135
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,867
- Wow! Good! So strong!
- So powerful!

136
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:19,467
Let's dance!

137
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,767
Girls!

138
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,467
And here she is.

139
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,400
Ladies and gentlemen...

140
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,967
the new manager of Bites
and Bottles,

141
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,567
Emma Joseco.

142
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,933
Thank you all
for being here tonight.

143
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:55,433
And please feel free
to indulge in our offerings.

144
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:59,800
And if there's anything we can
do to enhance your experience,

145
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,467
just let us know.

146
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,600
That's my girl.

147
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:05,667
By the way,

148
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:09,967
I'll introduce Senator
Hontiveros's wife to you.

149
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,267
Hello.

150
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,300
- Beautiful.
- Our madams.

151
00:12:13,433 --> 00:12:15,900
Wait for your turn, bosses.

152
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,833
Hi, Madam.

153
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:20,200
How are you?

154
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,667
Hello.

155
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:22,767
Cheers.

156
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:25,300
Cheers?

157
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:37,567
Nice.

158
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:38,900
How do you like the wine?

159
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:41,667
- Is it good? Thank you.
- Yeah.

160
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:53,400
Oh my god!

161
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:54,400
Man!

162
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:58,400
You've come a long way.

163
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,400
Two months?

164
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:01,800
What have you got on?

165
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:03,833
You learn fast.

166
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,567
I wouldn't be able to do
that without your help.

167
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,867
So, thank you, Logan.

168
00:13:10,133 --> 00:13:11,233
No, no, no.

169
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:15,767
This wouldn't happen if you
didn't cooperate with me.

170
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,500
I'm proud of you.

171
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:23,033
And when Jade sees you,
she'll be annoyed.

172
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:31,133
I'm sure Mookie will be
surprised when she sees me.

173
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:36,467
I wonder how she's doing.

174
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:42,167
I wasn't there
on her 18th birthday.

175
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:45,600
Is she still mad at me?

176
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:48,333
I wish I dared to face
my daughter.

177
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:50,800
I miss her so much, Logan.

178
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,700
DJ!

179
00:13:55,867 --> 00:13:57,667
One more, please!

180
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,467
That's Mookie's voice.

181
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:06,500
Are you sure?

182
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,267
Girls, dance!

183
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:21,067
Girls, dance!

184
00:14:45,767 --> 00:14:46,967
Mookie, let's go!

185
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:49,233
Why?

186
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:50,867
- Wait!
- Let's go!

187
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,433
- Come on!
- Wait, my bag!

188
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,267
- What was that?
- Let's go!

189
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:00,367
Are you sure?

190
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,167
Yes, I heard her.

191
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:13,667
You must be mistaken.

192
00:15:19,633 --> 00:15:20,933
What the hell, Zayn?

193
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,433
What's your problem?

194
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,567
Why are you interfering?

195
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,600
You were just a step away
from going wild over there.

196
00:15:29,733 --> 00:15:31,500
And so?

197
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:33,700
Mookie, what's going on
with you?

198
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,667
You're no longer
the Mookie I know.

199
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,367
You've changed a lot, Mooks.

200
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:44,967
Don't you want to be friends
with me anymore

201
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:47,067
because of that?

202
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,400
Is that it?

203
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,933
Then don't be friends with me!

204
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:55,300
I'm not forcing you if you
don't like who I am right now.

205
00:15:56,667 --> 00:15:58,833
Aunt Jade's there, anyway.

206
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:01,067
She's the only one who can
understand me.

207
00:16:02,933 --> 00:16:05,600
This is so annoying!
You know what, Zayn?

208
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,633
You just ruined my night.

209
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,033
I'm done here!

210
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:24,167
Love?

211
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:30,967
I sent you photos of possible
venues for our wedding.

212
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,100
Go and check it.

213
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:32,900
Sure.

214
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:33,667
Let me have that.

215
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,033
Okay. Careful, it's hot.

216
00:16:35,167 --> 00:16:38,200
Okay, I got it. Go, hurry!
Check it!

217
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,833
Ya!

218
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,233
- Yes, Ma'am?
- Please put this away.

219
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:44,867
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

220
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:48,433
Okay.

221
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:49,633
Thank you.

222
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:52,933
Did you see it?

223
00:16:53,067 --> 00:16:55,633
Everything is beautiful.

224
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,567
Why do you still have Emma's
picture on your phone?

225
00:17:06,667 --> 00:17:08,767
Didn't I tell you to delete
everything?

226
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:13,800
Jade, wait!

227
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,200
Love, I'm so sorry.

228
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:23,000
I didn't mean it.

229
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,233
It's your fault!

230
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:30,567
Didn't I tell you to delete
Emma's pictures on your phone?

231
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:34,200
How can you forget her
if everything's still there?

232
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,333
I'm sorry.

233
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:40,100
I'll delete it.

234
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:41,967
Sorry.

235
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,900
<i> Darn you, Emma.</i>

236
00:17:53,033 --> 00:17:55,133
<i> I hope you never come back.</i>

237
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:57,267
<i> I hope you're dead.</i>

238
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:04,000
I thought I saw her at the bar.

239
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:10,933
It's because you're always
thinking about Mookie.

240
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:12,767
Logan, she's changed a lot.

241
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:16,100
She's no longer the Mookie
I know.

242
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:18,167
Jade has already influenced her.

243
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:21,133
Too bad I wasn't there
to guide her.

244
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,267
Maybe that's why
she became like that.

245
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:26,600
Maybe it was wrong that
I didn't show up to her.

246
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,133
Emma.

247
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:34,433
Think about this.

248
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:39,267
They would bring you back

249
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,667
to Haven Wood
if you showed up to Mookie.

250
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:48,667
The new, strong, and brave Emma
I see now would not exist.

251
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:52,900
I'm sure Jade would have
overpowered you

252
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:55,800
if you stood before her
helpless.

253
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,100
I'm worried about Mookie.

254
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:09,067
It seems like she has something
heavy weighing on her heart.

255
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:13,000
And I wasn't there
to comfort her.

256
00:19:17,667 --> 00:19:19,633
You'll reunite
with your daughter.

257
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:25,433
Don't forget,
you now have what it takes.

258
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:29,333
You can handle Jade with ease.

259
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,433
Mookie!

260
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:48,033
Gosh, Stacy! Looks like
they're no longer friends.

261
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:50,867
Don't be so mean.

262
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,867
Hi, Mookie!

263
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:57,700
Why did you ignore Zayn?

264
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:00,933
You even stole him from me,
right?

265
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:03,000
Are you dumping him now?

266
00:20:03,167 --> 00:20:04,867
Poor guy.

267
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,800
You can have him all you want.

268
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:09,500
You can shove him
down your throat.

269
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,367
We're still talking.

270
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:18,867
No matter how you avoid me,
we will always see each other.

271
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,567
Aren't you going to join
the cheering squad?

272
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:24,400
I'm the captain there.

273
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,800
See you later at the open field.

274
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:33,433
See you at the open field,
Stacy.

275
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,033
Are you threatened?

276
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:38,200
Oh, no!

277
00:20:39,267 --> 00:20:40,867
You're threatened.

278
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,000
That's my territory.

279
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:45,733
First of all,
you no longer have friends.

280
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:48,433
Because you pushed them away,
remember?

281
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:54,467
FYI, Stacy.

282
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,867
I don't need a lot of friends.

283
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,133
Not like you.

284
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:03,300
You have many friends,
but they're fake.

285
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:05,067
Poor you.

286
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,467
It's okay.

287
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:12,033
See you at the open field!

288
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:20,533
<i>Let's see how brave you are when
I humiliate you in the tryout.</i>

289
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,633
Hello, love,
I'm almost done here.

290
00:21:27,767 --> 00:21:31,667
You can pick me up, and then we
can eat out for dinner. Okay?

291
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:32,933
Bye!

292
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:37,833
Emma?

293
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,200
Emma!

294
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,567
Cheers!

295
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:49,267
Emma?

296
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,100
- Emma!
- Ouch! What's wrong with you?

297
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:55,333
I'm so sorry.

298
00:21:56,033 --> 00:21:57,867
I thought you were
someone I knew.

299
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,933
Excuse me, I'm not Emma.

300
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:00,933
Sorry.

301
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,933
There will be a one-on-one
cheer dance today.

302
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:34,900
Wannabes versus the squad.

303
00:22:35,033 --> 00:22:36,000
Who wants to go first?

304
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:38,167
- Me.
- You versus me.

305
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:39,367
The squad captain.

306
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:40,733
G!

307
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,033
Bring it on.

308
00:22:42,167 --> 00:22:44,167
Do you think I won't notice
what you do?

309
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:45,200
You keep going out.

310
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:46,567
And drink.

311
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,400
You're no longer allowed
to leave the house!

312
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:49,800
Am I grounded?

313
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,267
Yes, you're grounded!

314
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,733
Just pretend that you obeyed
your dad.

315
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,600
I got you.

316
00:22:56,733 --> 00:22:59,700
You can still do everything
you want.

317
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:02,067
And I'll be the one
to cover for you.

318
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:05,433
- Thank you!
- You're welcome.

319
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:08,033
You only need to give them
a fright.

320
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:10,433
Let them see that you're very
much alive.

321
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:13,000
And that you won't get defeated.

322
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:17,033
You're ready to get
your child back.
